In rust use poem_openapi. For typescript `pnpm dev:openapi` (in the `packages/web` directory) uses the `openapi-typescript` library to generate a new typescript file.
Use tanstack query in combination with `openapi-hooks` (github.com/v3xlabs/openapi-hooks).
Write hooks as:
```tsx
export const getPostById = (post_id: string) => queryOptions({
  queryKey: ['post', '{post_id}', post_id],
  queryFn: async () => {
    const result = await apiFetch('/post/{post_id}', 'get', { params: {post_id: post_id}});

    return result.data;
  }
});
export const usePostById = (post_id: string) => useQuery(getPostById(post_id));
```